### Final architecture overview

Your platform eventually should resemble this structure:

```
Internet
   ↓
Cloudflare / CDN
   ↓
AWS Route53
   ↓
Application Load Balancer
   ↓
EC2 Instances (Docker)
   ↓
Nginx Reverse Proxy
   ↓
WordPress Containers (per client)
   ↓
Redis Cache
   ↓
AWS RDS MySQL
   ↓
S3 Storage (media + backups)
```

Supporting systems:

```
Monitoring → Prometheus + Grafana
Logs → Loki
Automation → Provisioning API (Node.js)
CI/CD → GitHub Actions
Infrastructure → Terraform
```

This architecture enables:

* multi-tenant hosting
* automated provisioning
* scalable traffic handling
* operational observability

